<div class="archive-container">
  <div class="archive-intro">
    <span class="archive-tag">Our Story</span>
    <h1 class="archive-title">About BSCF</h1>
    <div class="archive-line"></div>
    <p class="archive-lead">
      Bangladesh Socio-Cultural Forum (BSCF) is an independent, non-political, and non-profit platform 
      dedicated to the socio-cultural and educational development of Bangladeshi youth.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="about-content">
    <div class="main-description">
        <p>We focus on enhancing social skills, encouraging participation in cultural activities, promoting environmental awareness, and fostering tolerance and personal growth.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="vision-mission-grid">
      <div class="info-block">
        <h2 class="block-title">Our Vision</h2>
        <p class="block-text">
          BSCF envisions a Bangladesh where youth empowerment is paramount, ensuring their active 
          participation and influential voice in national development. We advocate for a tolerant 
          nation, emphasizing empathy and respect for diverse religions, perspectives, and beliefs.
        </p>
        <p class="block-text">
          Our goal is to cultivate socially responsible, environmentally conscious citizens with 
          cultural proficiency and a global mindset.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-block">
        <h2 class="block-title">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="block-text">
          BSCF engages youth from diverse backgrounds—villages, urban areas, grassroots, and 
          underprivileged regions—offering tangible behavioral skills, social responsibility, mental 
          health awareness, and cultural exchange opportunities.
        </p>
        <p class="block-text">
          We empower youth through volunteerism, fostering an environment where they emerge as 
          non-communal, respectful, humble, and tolerant global citizens advocating for sustainable development.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

